<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-621-336  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 621 336.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  July 9 1990 v7 n27 p60(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Cone revamps TransPortal tool, ships new library. (Cone Software'sTransPortal 1.4) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Musich, Paula.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Cone Software Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   TransPortal Pro (Program development software) (productintroduction)TransPortal 1.4 (Program development software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionProgram LibrariesMicro-Mainframe CommunicationProgram Development ToolsSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Paula MusichandM;Cone Software recently released a new programmers' library and an upgrade toits scripting tool designed to make it easier for corporate PC programmers toaccess mainframe and minicomputer data.andM;Cone's new TransPortal Pro library lets programmers create front ends to hostapplications using familiar PC languages such as dBASE.andP;  In addition, thecompany's enhanced script-writing software, TransPortal version 1.4, nowoffers support for more 3270 terminal-emulation software and eases theprocess of writing macros to automate host data entry or retrieval, saidDavid Hastings, president of the Boothwyn, Pa., company.andM;One early TransPortal 1.4 customer, the Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce,was able to create an automated data-transfer program in 10 days thateliminated the rekeying of data by eight data-entry clerks, according toGraham Barfoot, a vice president at the Toronto bank.andM;Unlike traditional front-end development tools that require users to learn adifferent programming language, the TransPortal Pro programmer's libraryallows developers to create fully interactive front ends using whateverlanguage they are familiar with, such as FoxPro, Clipper or C, according toHastings.andM;TransPortal 1.4, designed for sophisticated end users, guides users throughthe script-building process, notifying them when they make errors and helpingthem to fix those errors, officials said.andP;  The new release includes nativesupport for Digital Communications Associates Inc.'s IRMA 3270 terminalemulator, as well as support for IBM's FT Term file-transfer software.andM;Both tool sets are available now.andP;  Single-copy pricing is $1,595 forTransPortal version 1.4 and $1,495 for the Pro tool kit.andP;  Site licensing isalso offered; current TransPortal customers can upgrade for free.andM;Cone can be reached at (215) 497-0300.andO;</TEXT></DOC>